{
  "stem": "10010.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 36.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My grandmother's name was Freidle.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She comes from [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And her maiden name was [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And she had a sister in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Her name was Golda Amsterdamer-- married with children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "During a certain time when probably my mother was about 18, she lived with this aunt, because it was very hard for my grandmother and grandfather to, you know, to raise eight children.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "She lived there a short while-- I don't know how long-- at this [NON-ENGLISH]-- is Aunt [NON-ENGLISH]-- in her house, because they were well-off people.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They had a factory of-- of-- [LAUGHS] --of combs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But the combs were made of galalith.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It's a form of plastic.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I want to say also about my father's family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father's family, there was my grandfather.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My grandfather, he was born in Staszow, and he came from Staszow here.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had four children-- no-- four-- four son and a daughter-- five children.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The youngest was a daughter.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My grandmother died.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Her name was Tama, the same like mine.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he remarried and had with this other woman-- her name was [NON-ENGLISH]-- his name was Chaim-- Chaim Buchman-- and he had another four children-- two boys and two girls.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The boys' name was Itzhak and Mendel, and the girls who were younger, [NON-ENGLISH] and [NON-ENGLISH], who was in my-- my age.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, my grandfather was also a carpenter, and he worked very hard.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he had a place on a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was an apartment-- 1/2 was apartment where he lived-- a room-- a one room, really, with a kitchen.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he lives there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the other part, another big room is his place where he work on carpentry.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My father helped a lot.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "After he got married, he was helping this grandfather.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was bringing us very often there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Now, my father had four brothers from his-- like, his-- my grandfather's first wife.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He had four brothers, and the brother's name was Joseph, who later on lived in Belgium, and married, and had a son, Uri, who lives now in Israel.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He had another brother, Hersch, another brother Ephraim, and a sister, Shosha.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And this sister's daughter lives in Rishon, in Israel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "She has children and married.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "She was with us all the time until we came to Israel.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And during the war, her parents were with us as well.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "About the religious-- religious part.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Now, my parents, as I said, came from religious homes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But when they married, they rather were traditional.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "That on Rosh Hashanah and Yom Kippur they were going to-- to synagogue, but otherwise, not.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They had to work, both of them, on Saturdays.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And-- but when they-- they were very respectful to their parents.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And whenever the parents came to the house, we had a special kosher set of dishes.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And the parents ate on those dishes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "My-- my mother's father was a scribe-- was a Hasid.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And he was mostly, instead to attend to the business, which he had, they had also a business.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We-- we cannot call it business.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "They were working at home on-- on making buttons also from this galalith-- which was a platform of plastic-- making buttons.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "The sons were helping.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And my grandfather had a big beard.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "He was a lovely, very full of humor person.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "That's what they were telling me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "He rather would study Gemara, study Chumash, than a Torah, and scribe in the Torah, because he was a Torah scribe.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And this has to be done in calligraphy-- cannot be printed, the Torah.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And my grandmother was this energetic and working hard.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "My mother, when she was at home, also she had to help very much.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "My mother was extremely energetic, and she was-- she taught herself how-- how to sew by opening a pillow, opening a sheet, and sewing by herself the-- the pieces, of-- buying material and sewing.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And later on, she even opened sort of a school at home, and children-- young girls were coming to learn from her sewing.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "This way she support the younger sisters and brothers and also helped the parents as well.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I went when-- in my grade one, my parents send me to Hebrew school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the name of the school was Tarbut.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had a-- even a girlfriend whom I remember.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And her name was Hela Weisbrod-- that she was coming with me together to this-- to this school.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From grade one, from this time, I remember once that a teacher who taught us embroidery-- one day I forgot the embroidery.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was sewing only a paper, which was-- [LAUGHS] --printed there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she came to me and said, how come you doing?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was-- I started to cry.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This I remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
